102
00:04:24,950 --> 00:04:28,670
"At the corner of the carved balustrade,
the moon shines bright.

103
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:33,950
She loosens her silken robes
as the evening breeze caresses them.

104
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:38,520
Leaning by the red veil,
she counts the moonlit flowers' shadows.

105
00:04:38,670 --> 00:04:41,480
Little does she know
that spring has come for her."

106
00:04:42,390 --> 00:04:43,669
Excellent!

107
00:04:43,670 --> 00:04:44,599
That's good.

108
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,520
- Good!
- Good!

109
00:04:46,100 --> 00:04:47,530
- What a beautiful poem.
- Excellent!

110
00:04:53,530 --> 00:04:54,999
"Quiet Night Thoughts".
[*A poem by Li Bai]

111
00:04:54,999 --> 00:04:55,960
"Quiet Night Thoughts"?

112
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:57,229
Stop it.

113
00:04:57,230 --> 00:04:58,800
I forgot poems from elementary school.

114
00:05:06,230 --> 00:05:07,760
Reciting poems is boring.

115
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:38,840
Why is he playing the pipa like that?

116
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:47,109
ظآزThe sky is dim, like an evening drizzleظآز

117
00:05:47,110 --> 00:05:50,030
ظآزI'm waiting for youظآز

118
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:52,629
ظآزAs the cooking smoke drifts,
I lift the blind to the rainظآز

119
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:55,109
ظآزOnly a window separates us,
